A former administrator can now bury his wife who was murdered about three weeks ago. Paul Yatich, a former Kakamega District Commissioner, was yesterday given the green light to proceed with funeral plans for Loice Barsibet Yatich, whose body was found in her Kiplombe estate house in Eldoret on October 16. ALSO READ:

